### FINDINGS
[F-001-01] (a) Peck has a hard verify-loop ceiling: after any Fail, step 9 must be checked before retry, and 3+ verify loops triggers escalation; spec-kit only has “three fixes fail for the same symptom” and @debug “3+ hypotheses tested and rejected,” not a generic verify-loop budget. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:40-44`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:247-253`, `.opencode/agents/debug.md:453-468`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` escalation rules; possibly `CLAUDE.md` §4 escalation wording.

[F-001-02] (b) Peck escalates when the implementer cannot state, in one sentence, the root cause and why the fix addresses it; spec-kit requires root-cause tracing and @debug requires root-cause evidence/explanation, but does not make inability to state it an explicit escalation gate for normal sk-code verify loops. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:42-45`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:233-235`, `.opencode/agents/debug.md:483-497`, `.opencode/agents/debug.md:521-523`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADOPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` verify/debug loop; `CLAUDE.md` §4 escalation.

[F-001-03] (c) Peck treats “real codebase contradicts story” as a requirements/story amendment escalation, not a workaround; spec-kit has scope lock and a Logic-Sync halt for spec-vs-code contradictions, but lacks the explicit “amend the spec/story, do not code around it” instruction. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:17-19`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:45-47`; spec-kit: `CLAUDE.md:23-26`, `CLAUDE.md:310-316`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADOPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: `CLAUDE.md` Logic-Sync Protocol; system-spec-kit implementation/spec templates that distinguish amendment from workaround.

[F-001-04] (d) Peck has an explicit “reviewers contradict each other” escalation gate; spec-kit has generic contradiction handling but does not name contradictory reviewer outputs as a stop condition in sk-code/@debug. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:47-49`; spec-kit: `CLAUDE.md:310-316`, `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:247-253`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: `CLAUDE.md` Logic-Sync Protocol; `sk-code` formal-review integration notes.

[F-001-05] (e) Peck frames early escalation as cheaper than another verify loop; spec-kit says not to stop early and to keep going when safe, while separately escalating after low confidence/two failed attempts, so the cost-framing is missing and could reduce thrash if phrased as applying only after escalation criteria are met. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:16-19`; spec-kit: `CLAUDE.md:62-66`, `CLAUDE.md:314-316`. GAP: partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: `CLAUDE.md` Execution Behavior and Escalation; `sk-code` escalation rules.

### RULED_OUT
- Peck’s generic “review Fail is blocking; do not relabel Fail as partial” is not net-new against spec-kit’s no-completion-without-verification and mandatory test-output discipline. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:28-29`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:39-41`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:45`, `.opencode/agents/debug.md:533-539`.
- Peck’s “check escalation criteria before retrying” overlaps with spec-kit’s shipped self-check/adversarial validation discipline, so the novelty is the specific gates, not self-checking itself. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:40-42`; spec-kit: `.opencode/agents/debug.md:271-303`.
- Peck’s “work against real codebase, not assumptions” is already broadly covered by spec-kit’s research-first and real-data discipline. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:19`; spec-kit: `CLAUDE.md:59-66`.

